Hi Jenny,

If you're lucky you might be able put undersize bearings on the "new"
rod. You'd have to mic the crank journal to see if it is at an
available size, not out of round, and also look to see it is not
scored. Otherwise, yes, crank will need to be reconditioned if it is
still a good core.

John

